<br>
 Mighty Avengers goal is for everyone to have fun and enjoy the adventure of playing EverQuest. This guild has been built on a family basis and continues to grow due to the caring and fellowship found within. As with any family/guild there are some rules set up that as guild members you are expected to adhere to. Mighty Avengers is a well respected guild and as such these rules are set up as guidelines to keep it that way.<br>
<br>
Level Requirement: Main Character = 30<br>
                          Alt  = 5<br>
<br>
Two Officers minimum will interview prospective new members. Rules will be explained at the interview. If all parties agree a guild invite will ensue. The new member will be given the name of the recruiting officer to contact for added help on rules if needed. There will be a probation period of 30 days after which permanent membership will begin or the member will be explained why they are not accepted and asked to disband from the guild. <br>
<br>
Rules:<br>
<br>
1. Anonymous VS Roleplay: <br>
 Use roleplay so the guild tag shows. No one will see your class or level.  You are a Mighty Avenger be proud to show your guild name. This is not cause for guild removal but a matter of your honor.  <br>
<br>
2. No kill stealing (ksing), camp stealing, deliberate training: These are unacceptable actions from Guild members. Complaints against a member for this can result in guild removal after discussion with HC/Officers.<br>
<br>
<br>
3. Conduct: <br>
 Any complaints against members will be investigated, discussed by HC/Officers and warnings/action taken. A member will be warned about conduct before action is taken. Some complaints can result in guild removal. Your a member of an honorable guild your actions reflect on us all.<br>
<br>
<br>
4. No cussing:<br>
 Read your agreement with SOE you accept when you log on to EQ and go to the Sony site found there. You are a Representative of your guild conduct yourself as such. You never know who you may offend. This includes scrambled words that the intention is obvious. This also includes all chats except personal tells. <br>
<br>
5. No begging:<br>
 Do not beg for plat of for items. Begging is not respective to yourself or the guild. If you are in dire need of something check the bank for items you may need. If its for food or drink it doesn't take many green kills and selling to get enough for food and drink. If it is simply for an item you just want remember we all started with the same thing.<br>
<br>
6. Flaming/Verbal Abuse:<br>
Do not flame/argue in guild chat. If you have a problem with a fellow member do not disrupt guild chat. Take it to tells. If you need a mediator, get with an officer who will then go into group chat with all parties. If there is still a problem take it to the GL. All possible will be done to resolve the differences. The GL/Officers will be impartial and open minded.<br>
<br>
7. Teasing<br>
There is nothing wrong with old fashion teasing and bantering. This can be fun and keep guild chat lively. But please be attentive to the responses you receive. If it looks like someone is becoming upset or bothered by your remarks, cease immediately. If you upset a member unintentionally be a big enough person to apologize. If you have been upset tell that person and be as big a person as to accept the apology. Deliberately taunting a member may result in guild removal upon outcome of report to HC/Officers. <br>
<br>
<br>
 These are not hard rules so please abide by them. If you are reported to an officer for breaking one of these rules, you will be contacted by an officer(s) and a discussion will ensue. It will be noted as to the out come of the discussion. If it is deemed you did in fact break one of the rules you will be warned. Continued disregard of the rules will not be tolerated and can result in your being guild removed. This is not an option we like to take but will if necessary.<br>
<br>
If you have any questions please contact and Officer. Please check these rules for changes often. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bmightyavengers46623.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midlifecrysus>Midlifecrysus</A> at: 1/26/04 12:55 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><br><br><a self href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/fmightyavengers46623frm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/fmightyavengers46623frm22.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/fmightyavengers46623frm22.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/fmightyavengers46623frm22.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/fmightyavengers46623frm22.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub95.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>ju